WEBVTT

00:06.093 --> 00:08.356
[ Rock music plays ]

00:08.399 --> 00:09.531
Alright.

00:09.574 --> 00:11.359
Sumatra Sunrise,

00:11.402 --> 00:12.403
Harissa Honey,

00:12.447 --> 00:13.665
Turmeric Latte.

00:13.709 --> 00:15.319
I like them all.

00:15.363 --> 00:16.668
They're very soothing.

00:16.712 --> 00:19.062
Like the colors
you'd choose for a psych ward.

00:19.106 --> 00:20.498
Do you want to go back
to the browns then?

00:20.542 --> 00:23.066
I really don't.
Just paint it whatever you want.

00:23.110 --> 00:24.502
It's yourapartment.

00:24.546 --> 00:25.982
Yeah,
but this is your room.

00:26.026 --> 00:27.157
You know, you should choose.
It's --

00:27.201 --> 00:28.724
It's not mine, though.
It's...

00:30.595 --> 00:32.989
Yeah.
Uh, what do you think?

00:33.033 --> 00:35.905
Uh, oh, I think
you should hire a decorator.

00:35.948 --> 00:37.689
And I think we really need to
get to the station.

00:37.733 --> 00:40.736
The next 48 hours
are going to be crazy.

00:40.779 --> 00:41.911
Nice to see you again,
Tamara.

00:41.954 --> 00:42.999
Bye.

00:46.698 --> 00:48.526
[ Water runs ]

00:48.570 --> 00:50.920
Hey, do you think,
um, we're being silly --

00:50.963 --> 00:53.357
you know, taking this long
to pick a color.Not at all.

00:53.401 --> 00:55.794
Though I'd argue "we"
is the wrong pronoun to use.

00:55.838 --> 00:58.101
Tamara settled on a color
two weeks ago.

00:58.145 --> 01:00.103
And last week.
And Saturday.

01:00.147 --> 01:01.496
You vetoed them all.

01:01.539 --> 01:03.280
I did not.

01:03.324 --> 01:05.195
I just -- I just really
want to make sure

01:05.239 --> 01:06.675
that she's thinking
this through.

01:06.718 --> 01:08.546
You know, this is her home now.
It's her safe space.

01:08.590 --> 01:10.200
It needs to be perfect.

01:10.244 --> 01:12.333
Mm.
Oh, hey.
Don't forget your bag.

01:12.376 --> 01:13.986
Yeah.What the heck is in here?

01:14.030 --> 01:15.466
Books.

01:15.510 --> 01:16.989
Tim gave me a long list
of books to read

01:17.033 --> 01:18.382
to help me become
a training officer.

01:18.426 --> 01:21.472
According to him,
I have to up my Investigative IQ

01:21.516 --> 01:23.518
if I'm gonna make T.O.
in a year.
[ Sighs ]

01:23.561 --> 01:26.303
Is it weird for you that Tim
is officially no longer a T.O.?

01:26.347 --> 01:28.610
No. I mean, I'm moving on
with my career.

01:28.653 --> 01:30.394
And today so is he.

01:30.438 --> 01:32.875
Plus you secretly love it
that technically

01:32.918 --> 01:34.485
he's a rookie sergeant.

01:34.529 --> 01:36.661
Is he?
I hadn't thought of that.

01:40.274 --> 01:44.278
♪ Oh, whoa,
oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

01:44.321 --> 01:49.674
♪ I'm gonna win for you like
I know you want me to do ♪

01:49.718 --> 01:51.459
♪ Hey

01:51.502 --> 01:55.854
So, uh, rumor is
I am getting a new rookie today.

01:55.898 --> 01:57.813
Yeah, we need
to talk about him.

01:57.856 --> 01:59.162
Okay.
That doesn't sound good.

01:59.206 --> 02:00.598
[ Knock on glass ]

02:00.642 --> 02:02.644
You wanted to see me,
sir?
Yeah.

02:02.687 --> 02:04.385
I'm afraid I got a complaint

02:04.428 --> 02:05.995
about your uniform.

02:06.038 --> 02:07.910
Yeah. That Department-issued
sergeant's badge --

02:07.953 --> 02:09.346
that won't do.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.131
That is 80% tin.

02:11.174 --> 02:13.611
But this is solid silver
and real gold.

02:13.655 --> 02:15.787
Thank you.

02:15.831 --> 02:17.963
Sgt. Grey:
See, you earned it.

02:18.007 --> 02:19.704
I won't let you down.

02:19.748 --> 02:23.273
Sure you will.
This is a hard transition.

02:23.317 --> 02:25.797
You will fail
as much as you succeed.

02:25.841 --> 02:27.103
And you are
starting your watch

02:27.147 --> 02:28.757
on the craziest weekend
of the year.

02:28.800 --> 02:30.715
I can handle it.
I've been a supervisor before.

02:30.759 --> 02:31.890
Different animal.

02:31.934 --> 02:33.196
T.O.s are drill sergeants.

02:33.240 --> 02:35.329
Supervisors -- coaches.

02:35.372 --> 02:37.113
Orange slices, got it.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.420
Those stripes are Velcro,
Sergeant.

02:39.463 --> 02:41.335
Yes, sir.

02:41.378 --> 02:42.553
You'll do Roll Call today.

02:42.597 --> 02:45.339
Yes, sir.
I'll go get up to speed.

02:45.382 --> 02:46.427
Thank you.

02:46.470 --> 02:47.689
Good luck.

02:49.038 --> 02:51.127
Oh, uh,
w-what was my bad news?

02:51.171 --> 02:52.172
Your new rookie

02:52.215 --> 02:53.347
is Aaron Thorsen.

02:53.390 --> 02:54.870
[ Laughs ] Poor thing.

02:54.913 --> 02:55.871
If I had the same name

02:55.914 --> 02:57.133
as a tabloid murderer,

02:57.177 --> 02:58.569
I would definitely change it
immediately.

02:58.613 --> 03:00.832
Especially if I was
joining the LAPD.

03:00.876 --> 03:02.094
Yeah.

03:02.138 --> 03:04.140
But he's theAaron Thorsen.

03:04.184 --> 03:05.924
And he was exonerated.

03:05.968 --> 03:09.450
Okay. So the LAPD is just
letting anybody in now?

03:09.493 --> 03:11.713
No. Officer Thorsen had to sue

03:11.756 --> 03:13.236
to get into the Academy.

03:13.280 --> 03:15.151
But he earned solid scores
once there.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.371
And now
he is your new rookie.

03:17.414 --> 03:19.895
So, the question is:
Are you going to condemn him

03:19.938 --> 03:21.549
before you meet him,

03:21.592 --> 03:23.942
or give him five minutes
to prove he deserves to be here?

03:23.986 --> 03:25.988
If he can't hack it,
I will cut him.

03:26.031 --> 03:27.032
Lawsuit or no.

03:29.034 --> 03:30.906
[ Sighs heavily ]

03:33.082 --> 03:35.737
Oh, my God.
Do you know who that guy is?

03:35.780 --> 03:37.347
Um...

03:37.391 --> 03:38.348
Oh, that's the new rookie.

03:38.392 --> 03:39.393
We should introduce ourselves.

03:39.436 --> 03:41.003
Oh, no.

03:41.046 --> 03:43.310
Do you honestly
not recognize him?

03:43.353 --> 03:44.746
Is he not
the new rookie?

03:44.789 --> 03:47.314
That's Aaron Thorsen.

03:47.357 --> 03:48.793
Wha-- Rich kid.

03:48.837 --> 03:50.404
TikTok famous
before he got arrested

03:50.447 --> 03:52.057
for murdering
his roommate in Paris

03:52.101 --> 03:53.711
while he was
studying abroad.

03:53.755 --> 03:56.323
Right. Oh, right. God.
That trial went on forever.

03:56.366 --> 03:58.847
Trialsplural.
The case was a mess.

03:58.890 --> 04:00.457
The dynamics between
two of the investigators

04:00.501 --> 04:01.937
really drove
a lot of the issues.

04:01.980 --> 04:03.373
How do you know all that?

04:03.417 --> 04:05.070
I taught myself French
so I could follow the coverage.

04:06.507 --> 04:08.291
Of course you did.

04:10.293 --> 04:13.209
Officer Thorsen.
Yes, ma'am.

04:13.253 --> 04:14.776
I am Detective Nyla Harper,

04:14.819 --> 04:16.256
your training officer.

04:16.299 --> 04:17.909
Nice to meet you, ma'am.I would hold off

04:17.953 --> 04:19.302
on that sentiment.

04:19.346 --> 04:20.303
I'm gonna make this

04:20.347 --> 04:22.174
very hard on you.

04:22.218 --> 04:25.177
You are getting the equivalent
of five minutes today

04:25.221 --> 04:26.962
to prove to me
why your infamy

04:27.005 --> 04:29.312
doesn't make you a liability
to this Department,

04:29.356 --> 04:32.097
and a threat to my safety.Yes, ma'am.

04:32.141 --> 04:34.448
I will put your past
front and center

04:34.491 --> 04:36.188
because that
is what the public will do

04:36.232 --> 04:37.668
when we are
out on the street.

04:37.712 --> 04:41.106
So you better be squared away,
five minutes.

04:41.150 --> 04:43.370
Or your shift
will be over by lunch.

04:43.413 --> 04:44.980
Yes, ma'am.

04:45.023 --> 04:46.416
Mnh-mnh-mnh.

04:46.460 --> 04:47.983
Rookies sit
in the front row.

04:48.026 --> 04:49.506
Find me after.

04:49.550 --> 04:52.074
[ Officers conversing
indistinctly ]

04:55.556 --> 04:56.600
Sgt. Grey: Alright.

04:56.644 --> 04:58.167
As many of you know --

04:58.210 --> 05:00.430
we have a new sergeant
in the field today.

05:00.474 --> 05:03.999
Everyone,
Sergeant Tim Bradford.

05:04.042 --> 05:05.957
[ Cheers and applause ]

05:06.001 --> 05:08.482
Okay. Okay. Thank you.

05:08.525 --> 05:09.961
First up --

05:10.005 --> 05:11.615
we've got a new rookie --

05:11.659 --> 05:13.182
Officer Thorsen.
Stand up.

05:13.225 --> 05:14.531
Now, there's
a traditional introduction

05:14.575 --> 05:16.141
for probationary officers,

05:16.185 --> 05:18.143
but you are anything
but traditional.

05:18.187 --> 05:20.015
So I'm giving you 20 seconds
to introduce yourself

05:20.058 --> 05:21.625
before the rumor mill ramps up.

05:21.669 --> 05:22.626
Go.

05:22.670 --> 05:24.759
[ Clears throat ]

05:27.718 --> 05:30.330
I know there's nothing
that I can say in 20 seconds

05:30.373 --> 05:31.940
that'll change
the way you all view me.

05:31.983 --> 05:33.768
It's my actions
that will define me.

05:33.811 --> 05:35.683
And I promise to always
have your back,

05:35.726 --> 05:39.034
and I will always strive to tip
the scales towards justice...

05:40.905 --> 05:42.951
...because I know what
it's like when they're
tipped the other way.

05:42.994 --> 05:45.388
And I want to make
something very clear --

05:45.432 --> 05:48.696
Officer Thorsen
was found not guilty.

05:48.739 --> 05:51.176
He survived the Academy.
He earned the right to be here.

05:51.220 --> 05:53.265
Till Harper cuts him.[ Laughter ]

05:53.309 --> 05:54.832
Sit down.
Alright. Down to business.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.573
This weekend's gonna suck.

05:56.617 --> 05:58.358
We got the Dodgers
in the playoffs,

05:58.401 --> 05:59.924
six different concerts,

05:59.968 --> 06:01.317
a fancy art exhibit opening,

06:01.361 --> 06:02.927
and the Getty Gala
tomorrow night.

06:02.971 --> 06:04.712
Now, every A-list celebrity
with a pulse

06:04.755 --> 06:07.149
is gonna be there
in all their blinged out glory.

06:07.192 --> 06:09.020
Paparazzi are out
in full force.

06:09.064 --> 06:10.282
And we're getting requests
for additional security

06:10.326 --> 06:11.980
faster than
we can process them.

06:12.023 --> 06:14.591
Now, I've only seen the
potential for this much chaos

06:14.635 --> 06:17.159
one other time in my life,
and that was at an FOB in Iraq.

06:17.202 --> 06:19.204
So...good luck out there.

06:20.467 --> 06:21.859
Dismissed.

06:21.903 --> 06:24.427
♪♪

06:24.471 --> 06:26.647
Sgt. Grey: Were you trying
to get them to quit?

06:26.690 --> 06:29.084
Just keeping it real.

06:30.433 --> 06:32.087
Not enough orange slices?

06:33.828 --> 06:34.872
Let's go.

06:36.831 --> 06:40.312
Hey. What do you think
of wallpaper?
Love it!

06:40.356 --> 06:41.618
Because I'm not qualified
to hang it,

06:41.662 --> 06:43.490
so you'd have to
hire someone else.

06:43.533 --> 06:46.275
Mean.

06:46.318 --> 06:49.670
Lucy, you are the most
insightful person I know,

06:49.713 --> 06:51.976
you have to see
what's going on here --

06:52.020 --> 06:55.284
Why you can't decide how
to decorate Jackson's room.

06:55.327 --> 06:57.808
Until you make it okay
to move on,

06:57.852 --> 06:59.636
Tamara will never feel
like she belongs there.

06:59.680 --> 07:00.768
[ Engine revving ]

07:00.811 --> 07:02.770
Whoa. Whoa!

07:02.813 --> 07:03.814
She better be in labor.

07:03.858 --> 07:05.425
Control, 7-Adam-15,

07:05.468 --> 07:07.731
we have a reckless driver,
doing 70 down Hope.

07:07.775 --> 07:09.994
[ Siren wailing ]Possible 23-152.

07:10.038 --> 07:14.085
Plate: Three-Ocean-Edward-
Boy-Zero-Five-Eight.

07:14.129 --> 07:15.957
Dispatch:
Plate comes back clear

07:16.000 --> 07:18.263
and valid out of
Torrance to Acme industries.

07:18.307 --> 07:20.570
Oh, u-um...

07:20.614 --> 07:22.833
you mind if I practice T.O.'ing
during this traffic stop?

07:22.877 --> 07:25.662
You wanna
"work on your act" with me?

07:25.706 --> 07:27.272
Like I'm
a no-nothing rookie?

07:27.316 --> 07:28.665
Yeah.
Unless that would bother you?

07:28.709 --> 07:30.493
No. Not at all.

07:30.537 --> 07:31.668
Show me what you got.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.104
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

07:33.148 --> 07:34.889
Alright.

07:34.932 --> 07:37.021
How do we approach
a vehicle, Boot?

07:37.065 --> 07:39.894
Boot? Really?
Yeah. Sorry.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.330
As soon as it came out --Can we just --
Work with me.

07:41.373 --> 07:42.549
It sounded harsh even
just coming out of my --

07:42.592 --> 07:45.377
I feel terrible.
I'm starting again.

07:45.421 --> 07:47.162
How do we approach a vehicle,
Officer Chen?

07:47.205 --> 07:50.121
[ Chuckles ]
Using "Contact-Cover."

07:50.165 --> 07:52.384
Good work, Officer Chen. You
will take the Cover position.

07:52.428 --> 07:53.690
Copy that.

07:53.734 --> 07:55.126
Hey.
You're doing really great.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.476
Thanks.
[ Chuckles ]

07:58.956 --> 08:00.349
Good morning, Officer.

08:00.392 --> 08:02.046
Morning, ma'am.
You know why we pulled you over?

08:02.090 --> 08:03.526
I was speeding.

08:03.570 --> 08:04.614
70 in a 40 zone.

08:04.658 --> 08:06.311
It would be criminal

08:06.355 --> 08:08.618
to drive this car
at 40 miles an hour.

08:08.662 --> 08:10.315
The rules are the same
for all cars.

08:10.359 --> 08:14.015
No matter
how expensive they are.

08:14.058 --> 08:15.059
Officer Chen,
you're not in position.

08:16.539 --> 08:19.368
Now, may I see your license
and registration, please?

08:19.411 --> 08:21.718
You could run me, but then
it's gonna be this whole thing.

08:21.762 --> 08:25.200
So how about
I just say sorry and go?

08:25.243 --> 08:27.550
License and registration.
Now, please.

08:27.594 --> 08:29.987
[ Bag unzips ]

08:30.031 --> 08:31.249
[ Sighs ]

08:31.293 --> 08:33.817
Promise you won't freak out.

08:33.861 --> 08:34.992
I promise.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.867
Okay, Claire Ivey. Why don't you
step out of the vehicle for me?

08:39.910 --> 08:41.477
So I can be sure
you won't freak out

08:41.521 --> 08:42.783
and drive away
while I run your documents.

08:42.826 --> 08:45.568
Sure thing.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.091
Thank you.

08:51.748 --> 08:54.577
Mmm. I bet he looks
even better out of that uniform.

08:54.621 --> 08:56.884
What's he gonna find
when he runs you?

08:56.927 --> 08:58.276
A white whale.

09:01.236 --> 09:02.585
[ Static hisses ]

09:02.629 --> 09:04.587
Control, patch me
through to 7-Adam-100.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.720
The first lesson of
being a good supervisor --

09:06.763 --> 09:09.592
do not get to
the crime scene first.

09:09.636 --> 09:11.638
Getting to a scene first
can hurt their confidence

09:11.681 --> 09:13.509
and tells them
that you don't trust them.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.467
Yeah --Dispatch:
7-Adam-100, I have 7-Adam-15.

09:15.511 --> 09:17.295
[ Static hisses ]Patch him through.

09:17.339 --> 09:19.297
Uh, sir, I just pulled over
a driver for speeding,

09:19.341 --> 09:20.951
a Claire Ivey.

09:20.995 --> 09:22.605
She has
no outstanding warrants,

09:22.649 --> 09:24.999
but she is suspected
in a dozen

09:25.042 --> 09:27.610
multimillion dollar thefts
stretching back 20 years

09:27.654 --> 09:28.742
from L.A. to Hong Kong.

09:28.785 --> 09:29.743
The Regency diamond heist.

09:29.786 --> 09:31.092
[ Static hisses ]

09:31.135 --> 09:32.615
Nolan, Claire Ivey
has been a target of

09:32.659 --> 09:34.269
this Department
for over 10 years.

09:34.312 --> 09:37.098
Detective Lopez got close
to catching her in 2016,

09:37.141 --> 09:38.229
but a witness disappeared.

09:38.273 --> 09:40.057
Uh, it can't be a coincidence

09:40.101 --> 09:42.364
that she's in town on the
craziest weekend of the year.

09:42.407 --> 09:43.844
What do you want me to do?

09:43.887 --> 09:45.889
Cite her and let her know
she's officially on our radar.

09:45.933 --> 09:48.109
And, Nolan, impress on her

09:48.152 --> 09:50.546
that she should
get her ass out of town ASAP.

09:50.590 --> 09:55.638
Now is the time that
he tells me to leave town ASAP.

09:55.682 --> 09:56.813
Well, if he does,
you should listen.

09:56.857 --> 09:58.815
So?

09:58.859 --> 10:02.123
Suspected in 40 high-end
robberies, arrested for none.

10:02.166 --> 10:04.429
I'm impressed.
What brings you to L.A.?

10:04.473 --> 10:06.736
The weather.

10:06.780 --> 10:09.913
Well, I hear it's going to be
even nicer someplace else.

10:09.957 --> 10:12.046
Maybe you should try there
instead.

10:12.089 --> 10:14.352
[ Dramatic music plays ]

10:14.396 --> 10:17.529
So, does that mean
that I'm free to leave?

10:17.573 --> 10:19.227
You have a nice day.

10:19.270 --> 10:20.489
Thank you.

10:20.532 --> 10:24.624
♪♪

10:24.667 --> 10:26.060
What do you think?

10:26.103 --> 10:28.976
[ Vehicle engine starts,
tires squeal ]

10:29.019 --> 10:31.152
I think that I have
a girl crush.

10:33.241 --> 10:34.546
That's fair.

10:34.590 --> 10:37.419
[ Static hisses ]Control, 7-Adam-19.

10:37.462 --> 10:40.727
Show us on a welfare check
at 3312 Bronson.

10:40.770 --> 10:43.251
So, tell me,
Officer Thorsen,

10:43.294 --> 10:46.297
what are you gonna do if this
welfare check recognizes you?

10:46.341 --> 10:49.692
What I already do:
Nothing.

10:49.736 --> 10:52.521
And if she refuses to deal with
you because you're a murderer?

10:52.564 --> 10:56.264
I'm not a murderer, ma'am.
I was found innocent.

10:56.307 --> 10:58.788
Surely you're not naive to the
reality of false accusations.

10:58.832 --> 11:01.661
Especially against people
who look like us.

11:01.704 --> 11:05.055
How I feel personally about
your case is irrelevant here.

11:05.099 --> 11:08.537
My job is to assess your ability
to become a police officer.

11:08.580 --> 11:11.453
If every single call
is about you,

11:11.496 --> 11:14.412
then [chuckles] this is gonna
make it a lot harder to succeed.

11:14.456 --> 11:17.372
[ Doorbell rings ]

11:17.415 --> 11:18.721
Police!

11:18.765 --> 11:20.114
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

11:20.157 --> 11:20.941
Step back.

11:22.899 --> 11:25.032
Radio it in.

11:25.075 --> 11:25.989
[ Clears throat ][ Static hisses ]

11:26.033 --> 11:28.775
7-Adam-uh-19,

11:28.818 --> 11:30.646
we have signs of violence
on scene.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.996
Making entry.

11:34.781 --> 11:36.739
[ Door creaks ]

11:36.783 --> 11:41.483
♪♪

11:41.526 --> 11:45.574
[ Sniffs ]

11:45.617 --> 11:47.750
[ Sniffing ]
Yeah. That's gas.

11:47.794 --> 11:49.491
Holster your weapon.

11:49.534 --> 11:51.362
One spark,
this whole house goes up.

11:51.406 --> 11:54.104
[ Static hisses ]Control,
alert LAFD and SoCal

11:54.148 --> 11:55.410
we got a gas leak
at 3312 Bronson.

11:55.453 --> 11:57.281
Body.

11:57.325 --> 12:04.636
♪♪

12:04.680 --> 12:08.771
[ Coughing,
breathing rapidly ]

12:08.815 --> 12:12.601
[ Soft music plays ]

12:12.644 --> 12:14.516
There's no pulse.

12:14.559 --> 12:16.997
[ Coughs ]

12:17.040 --> 12:19.477
Alright, come on.
Go. Get out of here.

12:19.521 --> 12:21.131
[ Coughing ]

12:21.175 --> 12:22.350
[ Coughs ] Go!

12:22.393 --> 12:23.786
[ Coughing ]

12:23.830 --> 12:25.614
Control, 7-Adam-19,

12:25.657 --> 12:29.270
update this event to a 187,
alert Homicide and a supervisor.

12:29.313 --> 12:31.446
[ Inhales sharply,
coughs ]

12:31.489 --> 12:34.971
A murder on your first call
is a bad sign, five minutes.

12:35.015 --> 12:37.017
♪♪

12:40.324 --> 12:43.719
What do we have?Victim is Michaela Faris,
32 years old.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.895
Celebrity stylist.
Blunt force trauma to the head.

12:45.939 --> 12:47.549
And it looks like
whoever hit her

12:47.592 --> 12:49.551
turned on the gas
to make sure she stayed dead.

12:49.594 --> 12:50.813
Where's your rookie?

12:53.555 --> 12:55.339
Did he puke?

12:55.383 --> 12:57.080
Yeah. But it was more
than just the gore.

12:57.124 --> 12:58.386
You know,
it seems to have

12:58.429 --> 13:00.823
brought back
some uncomfortable memories.

13:00.867 --> 13:03.695
I don't know. It almost feels
like he shouldn't be a cop.

13:03.739 --> 13:05.872
Luckily he has the best
T.O. in the business
to help him through it.

13:05.915 --> 13:07.482
He can say that
now that I've been promoted.

13:07.525 --> 13:09.876
Will you stay focused
on the scene, Sergeant?

13:09.919 --> 13:10.833
[ Siren wailing ]Yes, sir.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.530
What's next?

13:12.574 --> 13:15.490
Well, we should canvass
while LAFD clears it.

13:15.533 --> 13:17.840
"We"?
You're supervisor on scene.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.450
A coach, not a player.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.322
You should stay here,
coordinate response.

13:21.365 --> 13:23.846
Right. Harper, grab your Boot,
go canvass the neighbors.

13:23.890 --> 13:25.065
Yes, sir.

13:28.590 --> 13:29.939
Harper.Hey.

13:29.983 --> 13:31.898
You get anything more
on Ivey?

13:31.941 --> 13:34.726
Car envy.[ Cellphone rings ]

13:34.770 --> 13:35.553
Excuse me. I got --

13:37.729 --> 13:39.862
Bailey, hey.

13:39.906 --> 13:42.517
John.Hey. We have a body inside.

13:42.560 --> 13:43.866
Can you get the gas off
from out here

13:43.910 --> 13:45.085
so we can
preserve the crime scene?

13:45.128 --> 13:47.043
Absolutely.
Mike, will you go take a look?

13:48.566 --> 13:50.307
Uh...how are you?

13:50.351 --> 13:52.005
Good. Uh, you?

13:52.048 --> 13:55.225
No. Good. Yeah.
I'm -- I'm -- I'm really good.

13:55.269 --> 13:57.314
Uh, I'm -- I'm Lucy.
We --

13:57.358 --> 14:00.230
I know. We met at the, um --
the wedding.

14:00.274 --> 14:02.537
Right.
Yeah. Of course.

14:02.580 --> 14:05.018
I should go help the guys.
They're useless without me.

14:05.061 --> 14:06.671
Right. No. Of course.
Uh, uh, great to see you.

14:06.715 --> 14:08.064
You too.

14:08.108 --> 14:12.373
[ Police radio chatter ]

14:12.416 --> 14:13.591
What happened
with you two?

14:13.635 --> 14:15.506
Oh. Nothing.

14:15.550 --> 14:17.378
Uh, this is the first
I've seen her since the wedding.

14:17.421 --> 14:19.119
I mean, we texted a few times
back and forth

14:19.162 --> 14:20.511
after I got back
from Guatemala --

14:20.555 --> 14:22.339
but then
there was the funeral.

14:22.383 --> 14:24.951
And really didn't seem the right
time to start something.

14:24.994 --> 14:29.825
So I -- Once I found my feet,
I just figured she moved on.

14:29.869 --> 14:33.089
Yeah. Well, I'd say
she's still kind of into you.

14:33.133 --> 14:35.091
You should
ask her out again.

14:35.135 --> 14:37.311
Look, I know
I screwed up back there.

14:37.354 --> 14:39.313
It was just
a little overwhelming.

14:39.356 --> 14:41.532
All this time you've been
trying to be a cop,

14:41.576 --> 14:42.925
it never occurred to you

14:42.969 --> 14:45.797
that you might have to
walk into a murder scene?

14:45.841 --> 14:47.321
I thought I was better.

14:47.364 --> 14:48.888
I haven't had an episode
like that in a while.

14:48.931 --> 14:50.454
But this is good.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.152
I found a trigger,
and I'm gonna work through it.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.284
This is not a therapy session,
four minutes.

14:54.328 --> 14:56.156
This is people's lives.

14:56.199 --> 14:58.158
Work through your issues
on your own time.

15:00.595 --> 15:03.076
Narrator: And it was on
that cold Paris night

15:03.119 --> 15:06.949
that Aaron Thorsen's
life changed forever,

15:06.993 --> 15:08.864
accused by French prosecutors

15:08.908 --> 15:11.171
of committing the gruesome
murder of his roommate

15:11.214 --> 15:13.216
and long-time friend
Patrick --

15:13.260 --> 15:15.131
Jack is
finally, finally down.

15:15.175 --> 15:17.264
Who knew rocking him to sleep
in this would actually work?

15:17.307 --> 15:18.743
Of course it works.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.354
It's an unwashed hoodie
reeking of the person

15:20.397 --> 15:22.269
he loves most
in the world.
[ Chuckles ]

15:22.312 --> 15:24.445
You know you're gonna
be wearing that every
day from now on, right?

15:24.488 --> 15:26.316
We should try to
get some sleep while we can.

15:26.360 --> 15:27.970
I just need to finish watching
this episode.

15:28.014 --> 15:29.580
[ Dramatic music plays]

15:29.624 --> 15:32.148
Why are you watching
a docuseries on Aaron Thorsen?

15:32.192 --> 15:34.107
He's Harper's new rookie.

15:34.150 --> 15:35.891
I leave for a month, and they
start letting in French killers.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.893
He's American.
And he was found not guilty.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.155
After he was found guilty.

15:39.199 --> 15:40.983
Yeah.
The defense was a joke.

15:41.027 --> 15:42.985
If I'd have been his lawyer,
wouldn't have gone to trial.

15:43.029 --> 15:46.119
[ Jack crying ]

15:47.859 --> 15:49.426
I got this.
You, get some sleep.

15:51.428 --> 15:55.171
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

15:55.215 --> 15:56.694
Hey.

15:56.738 --> 15:58.479
Hey. It's John and Lucy.
Is this a good time?

15:58.522 --> 15:59.741
Does that
even exist anymore?

15:59.784 --> 16:01.003
How's the baby?

16:01.047 --> 16:02.657
He's great.

16:02.700 --> 16:04.659
A bit of a nightmare.
I haven't slept in two days.

16:04.702 --> 16:06.878
Yikes. Okay.
We'll make this fast.

16:06.922 --> 16:09.533
Uh, you worked a case involving
Claire Ivey a few years ago.

16:09.577 --> 16:11.579
Let me guess,
she's our new captain.

16:11.622 --> 16:14.364
What? No. But she is in town.
We pulled her over this morning.

16:14.408 --> 16:16.105
I've never been so grateful
for maternity leave.

16:16.149 --> 16:18.368
Is she that bad?She's that good.

16:18.412 --> 16:19.761
Claire will pull
some impossible heist

16:19.804 --> 16:20.805
and leave you
looking like fools.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.198
Just like she did to me.

16:22.242 --> 16:23.852
Okay. Any insights?

16:23.895 --> 16:25.419
She doesn't carry a crew.

16:25.462 --> 16:27.290
Always hires locals
for the job.

16:27.334 --> 16:30.641
Getaway driver, hacker,
muscle, demolitions expert.

16:30.685 --> 16:32.513
Back in the day, I put together
a list of people she likes.

16:32.556 --> 16:34.689
Check that file.Will do.
Thank you for your help.

16:34.732 --> 16:36.517
A-And get some sleep.Thank you.

16:36.560 --> 16:38.127
[ Cellphone beeps ]

16:38.171 --> 16:40.477
Oh, Bailey.

16:40.521 --> 16:42.827
Hey. Ask her out.

16:42.871 --> 16:44.177
I...

16:44.220 --> 16:45.613
Hey.

16:45.656 --> 16:47.789
Um...

16:47.832 --> 16:50.444
She had to pee.
We all good inside?
Yeah.

16:50.487 --> 16:52.272
We turned the gas off --
the house is venting --

16:52.315 --> 16:54.100
I'd give 10, 15
before you let anyone in.

16:54.143 --> 16:56.058
Okay. Great. Thank you.
Uh, Bailey.

16:56.102 --> 16:57.842
I think you're great,

16:57.886 --> 16:59.931
and I feel like we didn't
really, uh, get a chance

16:59.975 --> 17:03.544
because of just every--
everything that happened.

17:03.587 --> 17:06.373
And I feel like I would l-live
the rest of my life

17:06.416 --> 17:08.810
full of regret
if I didn't take every advantage

17:08.853 --> 17:10.812
of the universe apparently
pushing us back together,

17:10.855 --> 17:14.250
a-and -- and just see
if you wanted to try again.

17:14.294 --> 17:17.253
You know? Just a date. I'm not
gonna ask you to marry me.

17:17.297 --> 17:18.994
Which, you know,
I don't have to say that.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.083
I'm suddenly nervous.
I'm gonna stop talking.

17:23.129 --> 17:26.436
Well, I can't have you living
with regret for all of eternity.

17:26.480 --> 17:27.611
Let's do it.

17:27.655 --> 17:30.614
Okay.
Uh, how's, um --

17:30.658 --> 17:33.052
Tonight?Tonight. Great.

17:33.095 --> 17:34.096
I'll text you.

17:36.359 --> 17:38.535
Tim: Alright. Claire Ivey
doesn't get out of bed

17:38.579 --> 17:40.624
for anything less than
a $5-million payday.

17:40.668 --> 17:42.496
The problem is: There are
a dozen targets in L.A.

17:42.539 --> 17:44.193
this weekend
that meet that criteria.

17:44.237 --> 17:48.067
Including the Rothko exhibit
at LACMA and the Getty Gala.

17:48.110 --> 17:50.678
Well, that Gala is gonna be
crawling with private security.

17:50.721 --> 17:53.420
You know, the chaos of this
weekend could just be a cover

17:53.463 --> 17:55.813
to hit a traditional target
while we're stretched thin.

17:55.857 --> 17:57.859
Or she could be trying
to hit a private home.

17:57.902 --> 17:59.643
I mean, I used to party with
kids in high school

17:59.687 --> 18:02.864
whose parents had millions in
cash and jewelry in their homes.

18:02.907 --> 18:05.345
The challenge is a part
of the thrill for her.

18:05.388 --> 18:07.042
After all these years,
I'd think Claire would want

18:07.086 --> 18:09.262
something worthy of her skill --
not just a payday.

18:09.305 --> 18:10.741
Do we know
where she is now?

18:10.785 --> 18:12.395
Yeah.
Hiding in plain sight.

18:12.439 --> 18:14.745
Booked a suite
at a hotel in Century City.

18:14.789 --> 18:16.791
What about her crew?
Did we run that list of
names Lopez gave us?

18:16.834 --> 18:18.358
No, we don't have to.
Head of security for the hotel

18:18.401 --> 18:20.011
is ex-LAPD.

18:20.055 --> 18:22.318
We managed to I.D. her crew
from the elevator cam.

18:22.362 --> 18:24.799
Sgt. Grey: Jamie Carr.
Evan Rando.

18:24.842 --> 18:27.149
Sadi Ling.
Allan Gibson.

18:27.193 --> 18:30.413
First non-binary person to hack
the New York Stock Exchange.

18:30.457 --> 18:32.198
Explosives expert --

18:32.241 --> 18:33.460
Learned the demolitions trade
from her family business

18:33.503 --> 18:35.026
bringing down
condemned buildings.

18:35.070 --> 18:37.290
Now she blows safes.Gun for hire.

18:37.333 --> 18:39.640
Former British SAS
turned private contractor.

18:39.683 --> 18:41.468
Getaway driver.

18:41.511 --> 18:42.730
Was an up and comer
on the NASCAR circuit

18:42.773 --> 18:44.253
until he failed
a string of drug tests.

18:44.297 --> 18:46.386
What's the game plan,
Sergeant Bradford?

18:46.429 --> 18:47.909
Well, there's no sense
in being covert.

18:47.952 --> 18:49.476
She knows we're onto her.

18:49.519 --> 18:51.173
So I'd put black and whites
on her hotel,

18:51.217 --> 18:52.087
and on every person
in her crew.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.915
Let them see us.

18:53.958 --> 18:55.177
Maybe one of them
will get cold feet,

18:55.221 --> 18:56.483
she'll have to
call it off.

18:56.526 --> 18:58.659
Nolan, Chen,
she's already met you,

18:58.702 --> 19:00.269
so park yourselves
outside her hotel.

19:00.313 --> 19:02.141
Harper,
you want in on this?

19:02.184 --> 19:04.491
Uh, yeah. But Officer Thorsen
isn't ready yet.

19:04.534 --> 19:06.014
I can handle it,
ma'am.

19:06.057 --> 19:07.755
That is my call,
and I say that you can't.

19:07.798 --> 19:10.497
So you will be working the front
desk for the rest of your shift.

19:10.540 --> 19:12.673
I can't prove myself to you
if I'm not with you.

19:12.716 --> 19:14.936
You can't
get me killed either.

19:14.979 --> 19:17.591
Alright.
Let's get back out there.

19:17.634 --> 19:20.246
[ Officers conversing
indistinctly ]

19:20.289 --> 19:22.552
You still looking
for wallpaper?

19:22.596 --> 19:26.252
No. I am trying to figure out
where Claire got the dress

19:26.295 --> 19:28.558
she was wearing
in that surveillance photo.

19:28.602 --> 19:31.300
Found it.
Ugh, it's so expensive.

19:31.344 --> 19:33.215
She's a criminal,
not a role model.

19:33.259 --> 19:34.956
Who says
she can't be both?

19:34.999 --> 19:37.132
She is brilliant,
career-oriented --

19:37.176 --> 19:38.133
Evil.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.614
[ Scoffs ] Listen.

19:40.657 --> 19:43.834
Her drive, my morality, we could
solve the world's problems.

19:43.878 --> 19:46.446
Oh, hey! Where are you
taking Bailey tonight?

19:46.489 --> 19:48.839
Oh, um...Earthing.

19:48.883 --> 19:50.319
Ben recommended it,

19:50.363 --> 19:54.323
so if nothing else,
it'll be expensive.

19:54.367 --> 19:55.455
You're nervous.

19:55.498 --> 19:57.370
I know.
I-I like her.

19:57.413 --> 19:59.546
She's just --Oh, there's Claire.

19:59.589 --> 20:02.462
♪♪

20:02.505 --> 20:03.767
[ Groans ]

20:05.856 --> 20:07.902
You know the spa here
is amazing.

20:07.945 --> 20:09.773
You really should try it.

20:09.817 --> 20:13.124
Oh. So while we get a massage,
you'll, what, steal a Monet?

20:13.168 --> 20:15.126
A Monet?

20:15.170 --> 20:18.304
What am I, a teenage girl from
the '80s decorating my room?

20:18.347 --> 20:20.567
But there is a Jeff Koons
at the Broad that would look

20:20.610 --> 20:22.917
phenomenal at my house in Vail,
so [clicks tongue]

20:22.960 --> 20:25.963
I bet.
But you've hit museums before.

20:26.007 --> 20:27.661
You're looking
for something new.

20:27.704 --> 20:29.576
Someone has been
doing their homework.

20:29.619 --> 20:31.186
Yes, I have.
Thank you.

20:31.230 --> 20:33.667
So, if you're not into Monets,
what is it?

20:33.710 --> 20:35.973
You can't honestly think
you're going to stop me.

20:36.017 --> 20:37.540
I mean, I've gone up against

20:37.584 --> 20:39.977
the best law enforcement
agencies in the world.

20:40.021 --> 20:41.327
Well,
if you're so confident,

20:41.370 --> 20:42.502
why don't you just
give us a hint?

20:42.545 --> 20:44.286
I know you love
a challenge.

20:44.330 --> 20:46.375
Okay. Here's your hint:

20:46.419 --> 20:48.116
By the end of the day
tomorrow,

20:48.159 --> 20:49.900
I will be buying
a private island

20:49.944 --> 20:52.338
and you'll be doing paperwork
and feeling sad.

20:52.381 --> 20:53.774
So the heist is tomorrow?

20:53.817 --> 20:55.906
Sure.
Or I'm just messing with you.

20:55.950 --> 20:58.474
Have a lovely evening.

20:58.518 --> 21:00.084
♪♪

21:03.349 --> 21:05.699
Oh, hey.
How was the, uh, front desk?

21:05.742 --> 21:07.483
Great. How was the stakeout?
Do you need something from me?

21:07.527 --> 21:10.007
Yeah. I heard the front desk
was anything but great.

21:10.051 --> 21:12.619
How many people asked
if you were a murderer?

21:12.662 --> 21:14.055
Nine.
Uh-huh.

21:14.098 --> 21:16.623
And TMZ showed up?
Briefly.

21:16.666 --> 21:18.451
That's a problem,
don't you think?

21:18.494 --> 21:20.453
No. Not for me, ma'am.
I can handle it.

21:22.019 --> 21:23.760
Unless you're gonna cut me
from the program.

21:23.804 --> 21:25.762
No.
I'm not gonna fire you.

21:25.806 --> 21:28.287
No. I don't have to.

21:28.330 --> 21:30.071
'Cause you are
gonna go home tonight,

21:30.114 --> 21:31.899
and you are not
gonna sleep.

21:31.942 --> 21:34.336
'Cause you are gonna keep
thinking about that woman's body

21:34.380 --> 21:37.383
and the panic that you felt
when we found her.

21:37.426 --> 21:40.255
And you will realize that you
are going to feel that panic

21:40.299 --> 21:42.605
every day at this job.

21:42.649 --> 21:46.783
And then you'll come in
early tomorrow -- and quit.

21:46.827 --> 21:49.133
And if you don't quit,

21:49.177 --> 21:51.614
thatis when
I will fire you.

21:51.658 --> 21:53.573
[ Soft music plays ]

21:53.616 --> 21:54.574
That's not fair --

21:54.617 --> 21:58.534
I am doing you a favor.

21:58.578 --> 22:00.754
There is honor
in resigning.

22:00.797 --> 22:03.191
In realizing that
you are not up for this.

22:03.234 --> 22:06.281
But if you get fired
from this job,

22:06.325 --> 22:07.717
what comes next, hmm?

22:07.761 --> 22:10.720
The embarrassment,
the shame, the ridicule.

22:10.764 --> 22:13.157
And, Officer Thorsen,

22:13.201 --> 22:16.900
haven't you been through enough
ridicule for one lifetime?

22:16.944 --> 22:19.425
[ Breathes deeply ]

22:19.468 --> 22:21.122
Right.

22:22.515 --> 22:25.996
We're getting off track.
These are the facts we know.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.302
Aaron and Patrick
were roommates,

22:27.346 --> 22:28.869
studying abroad in Paris.

22:28.912 --> 22:30.349
Yeah,
but not just roommates.

22:30.392 --> 22:32.046
Friends who had known each other
since childhood.

22:32.089 --> 22:35.179
Right.
But then Patrick brings home

22:35.223 --> 22:36.616
a girl from the club
one night.
Mm-hmm.

22:36.659 --> 22:38.400
After a few hours,
she leaves.

22:38.444 --> 22:40.402
We know she leaves
because of the security footage

22:40.446 --> 22:41.882
from across the street.

22:41.925 --> 22:43.274
And the next morning,
Aaron wakes up,

22:43.318 --> 22:44.972
goes to the bathroom,
finds Patrick's body

22:45.015 --> 22:46.408
on the tile floor
with his throat cut open.

22:46.452 --> 22:50.064
Or Aaron was the one
who slit Patrick's throat,

22:50.107 --> 22:52.893
after she left.W-- And then waited till
the next day to call the cops?

22:52.936 --> 22:54.329
No, no, no.
She did it.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.287
Or her jealous boyfriend,

22:56.331 --> 22:57.637
whose whereabouts
were never established.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.160
And Aaron
somehow heard nothing?

22:59.203 --> 23:00.074
He was knocked out
on painkillers.

23:00.117 --> 23:01.380
You saw the texts.

23:01.423 --> 23:03.686
By the end,
Aaron hated Patrick.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.253
No, look.
Texts mean nothing.

23:05.296 --> 23:06.733
They were roommates,
they argued.

23:06.776 --> 23:08.996
The media
was trying to paint Aaron

23:09.039 --> 23:10.606
as some spoiled kid
who committed murder

23:10.650 --> 23:12.521
because he didn't want to
do his share of the chores.

23:12.565 --> 23:16.438
Or because he did them
so badly.

23:16.482 --> 23:19.354
Okay. Loading the dishwasher
can be complicated.

23:19.398 --> 23:22.792
[ Jack crying ]

23:22.836 --> 23:25.142
We are so stupid.

23:25.186 --> 23:27.275
We could've showered.
We could've changed clothes.

23:27.318 --> 23:30.191
We could've slept.
What is wrong with us?

23:33.368 --> 23:34.761
Am I interrupting?

23:34.804 --> 23:36.458
[ Exhales sharply ]
Please, interrupt.

23:36.502 --> 23:38.155
College is so hard.

23:40.506 --> 23:41.985
Um...

23:42.029 --> 23:44.640
I'm -- I'm sorry.

23:44.684 --> 23:47.426
I've been so picky
about the paint color.

23:47.469 --> 23:48.775
It's stupid.

23:48.818 --> 23:50.429
Whatever, it's cool.

23:50.472 --> 23:53.214
No. It's not.

23:53.257 --> 23:55.564
I think I've just been having,
like, a really hard time,

23:55.608 --> 23:56.609
because...

23:56.652 --> 23:59.220
[ Soft music plays ]

23:59.263 --> 24:01.222
You know,
it makes it real, that...

24:01.265 --> 24:03.529
[ Inhales shakily ]

24:03.572 --> 24:05.444
...that he's never coming home
and...

24:07.446 --> 24:08.664
I'm sorry.

24:08.708 --> 24:09.926
I know.

24:12.538 --> 24:15.323
[ Breathes deeply ]

24:15.366 --> 24:18.282
Every time
I change something,

24:18.326 --> 24:20.633
it just feels like
I'm erasing him.

24:20.676 --> 24:23.070
I want to be happy
that I'm living here...

24:25.420 --> 24:27.770
...but I can't stop feeling
guilty that he's not.

24:27.814 --> 24:29.946
He would want you here.

24:29.990 --> 24:33.602
He would want something good
to come out of this.

24:33.646 --> 24:35.256
This is good.

24:35.299 --> 24:37.214
And he would mock us,
endlessly.

24:37.258 --> 24:40.261
I mean, look at this place.
[ Laughs ]

24:40.304 --> 24:41.871
It's kinda growing on me.

24:41.915 --> 24:44.091
Yeah, like a fungus.

24:45.962 --> 24:49.836
Please. Do whatever you want
in this room.

24:49.879 --> 24:51.228
Whatever I want?

24:51.272 --> 24:52.665
Yes?

24:52.708 --> 24:54.101
[ Laughs ]

24:54.144 --> 24:55.798
[ Sighs ]
I mean, yes. Yes.

24:55.842 --> 24:56.886
Let's think about it.

24:56.930 --> 24:58.018
[ Doorbell rings ]

25:00.934 --> 25:02.892
Hi.
Hi.

25:02.936 --> 25:04.067
Come in.
Thanks.

25:04.111 --> 25:05.678
You look beautiful.

25:05.721 --> 25:08.985
I'd better. My entire closet
is on my bedroom floor.

25:09.029 --> 25:11.335
I spent two hours looking
for the perfect outfit --

25:11.379 --> 25:13.555
which said interested
but not desperate.

25:13.599 --> 25:15.775
Hot but not too hot.

25:15.818 --> 25:16.819
Mission accomplished.

25:16.863 --> 25:18.560
You look very handsome.

25:18.604 --> 25:20.954
Thank you.
Um, first thing I put on.

25:20.997 --> 25:22.956
God, it must be nice
to be a man.

25:22.999 --> 25:24.479
So where are we going?

25:24.523 --> 25:26.220
A new restaurant
in Silver Lake.

25:26.263 --> 25:28.875
Apparently all their entrées
are made from mung beans.

25:28.918 --> 25:32.226
Cool.
Um...what's a mung bean?

25:32.269 --> 25:35.142
I believe
it's a legume of a sort.

25:35.185 --> 25:36.883
I think -- Honestly,
I-I picked it

25:36.926 --> 25:38.319
just so
I would appear hip.

25:38.362 --> 25:40.408
Mm. I've dated hip guys.
It's exhausting.

25:40.451 --> 25:42.584
Oh.
But I'm sure
the place'll be great.

25:42.628 --> 25:44.586
Okay, um...

25:44.630 --> 25:45.935
How about
I give you the option?

25:45.979 --> 25:47.981
Uh, we can go
eat mung beans --

25:48.024 --> 25:49.678
So delicious.

25:49.722 --> 25:52.725
Or -- how would you feel
about going on a stakeout?

25:52.768 --> 25:54.596
Oh, hell yeah.

25:54.640 --> 25:57.207
[ "Irresistible" plays ]Okay. Let's do this.

25:57.251 --> 25:58.339
Yes.

25:58.382 --> 26:00.428
♪ Help myself

26:00.471 --> 26:02.343
♪ Can't take my eyes off you

26:02.386 --> 26:04.301
Oh, finally.
Here we go.

26:04.345 --> 26:06.434
Thank you.You're allowed to drink
on a stakeout?

26:06.477 --> 26:09.350
Cops have all the fun.Oh. I'm not on duty.

26:09.393 --> 26:10.960
There's cars waiting
at every exit

26:11.004 --> 26:12.179
to follow her
the second she leaves.

26:12.222 --> 26:13.659
She?
Mm.

26:13.702 --> 26:16.096
Okay.
Over my left shoulder.

26:16.139 --> 26:18.185
Mm-hmm.Tall blonde, great dress.

26:18.228 --> 26:20.143
I don't know how
to tell you this.

26:20.187 --> 26:21.231
But that's my sister.

26:21.275 --> 26:22.581
[ Spits ]

26:22.624 --> 26:24.452
I'm --
[ Laughing ] I'm kidding.

26:24.495 --> 26:25.496
I'm kidding.
[ Coughs ]

26:25.540 --> 26:26.802
Oh, my God, your face.

26:26.846 --> 26:28.195
That was convincing.

26:28.238 --> 26:31.111
Or maybe
you are just too trusting.

26:31.154 --> 26:32.460
♪ Till we hanging at the top

26:32.503 --> 26:35.768
Fancy seeing you here,
Officer Nolan --

26:35.811 --> 26:37.857
or can I call you John?

26:37.900 --> 26:40.555
What kind of
alleged master thief would I be

26:40.599 --> 26:41.991
if I didn't do my homework?

26:42.035 --> 26:43.471
[ Chuckles ]

26:43.514 --> 26:45.473
He's divorced. One kid.

26:45.516 --> 26:48.868
Moved here two years ago
from Foxburg, Pennsylvania,

26:48.911 --> 26:49.912
to become a cop,
and you have been

26:49.956 --> 26:51.261
in the headlines ever since.

26:51.305 --> 26:53.524
But, you, I-I don't know.

26:53.568 --> 26:55.788
And you won't.

26:55.831 --> 26:57.964
Who's your friend
in the silky shirt?

26:58.007 --> 27:00.401
He's not one of your crew --
we've I.D.'d them already.

27:00.444 --> 27:03.491
Unless you need someone even
more specialized for this job.

27:03.534 --> 27:06.363
Perhaps a pilot?
Expert spelunker?

27:06.407 --> 27:08.322
He's a dentist.

27:08.365 --> 27:09.758
Well, it's getting late.

27:09.802 --> 27:11.847
I should get to bed.
It is a busy day tomorrow.

27:11.891 --> 27:13.153
Enjoy those drinks.

27:13.196 --> 27:14.676
See you in the morning.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.504
Probably not.

27:16.547 --> 27:17.984
Really nice to meet you.

27:18.027 --> 27:19.986
♪ Can't help myself

27:20.029 --> 27:21.117
♪ Can't help myself

27:21.161 --> 27:24.251
Well, I guess
that stakeout's over.

27:24.294 --> 27:26.514
Yes. The stakeout's
definitely over.

27:26.557 --> 27:30.039
But that doesn't mean
that the date has to be.

27:30.083 --> 27:32.433
No. It doesn't.

27:32.476 --> 27:34.261
♪ You got that irresistible

27:34.304 --> 27:35.044
♪ Ooh

27:50.364 --> 27:53.106
Is this a sneaking out
full of regret thing,

27:53.149 --> 27:54.760
or a letting me sleep
thing?

27:54.803 --> 27:58.285
Letting you sleep thing.Oh, well.
In that case, I'm awake.

27:58.328 --> 28:00.679
I know it's early, I have
a capoeira class to teach.

28:00.722 --> 28:02.419
I'd ask to join you, but I don't
think you should see me

28:02.463 --> 28:03.638
fall on my ass
till our second date.

28:03.682 --> 28:05.335
Second?

28:05.379 --> 28:07.294
Technically,
this is date number three.

28:07.337 --> 28:09.731
Oh. Is it too early
to ask for date number four?

28:09.775 --> 28:11.341
Let me get some coffee
in me first.

28:13.604 --> 28:15.345
I'll call you later.Okay.

28:15.389 --> 28:16.564
Bye.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.351
[ Knock on door ]You got a minute, sir?

28:21.395 --> 28:24.137
Sure.

28:24.180 --> 28:26.139
Where's your rookie?Oh. In a perfect world,

28:26.182 --> 28:27.967
he is about to walk in here
and resign.

28:28.010 --> 28:30.404
I want you
to not stop him.

28:30.447 --> 28:32.406
I heard that you asked
for him to be assigned here.

28:32.449 --> 28:34.582
I did. A wise captain
once taught me that

28:34.625 --> 28:37.237
there's value in having rookies
with unique perspectives.

28:37.280 --> 28:38.934
With all due respect, sir,
there is unique,

28:38.978 --> 28:40.806
and then
there's Aaron Thorsen.

28:40.849 --> 28:43.199
Look, you need to --

28:43.243 --> 28:46.072
Who clearly isn't
walking in here to resign.

28:48.509 --> 28:50.119
Man: Hey, Aaron.
Good morning.

28:51.425 --> 28:52.818
Why are you dressed?

28:52.861 --> 28:54.123
Didn't I tell you
what would happen to you

28:54.167 --> 28:55.690
if you didn't
turn in your papers?

28:55.734 --> 28:57.344
Then cut me.

28:57.387 --> 28:59.346
I know you think I'm just
some privileged train wreck

28:59.389 --> 29:01.391
who sued his way into the
Department to play dress up,

29:01.435 --> 29:03.002
but I'm not.

29:03.045 --> 29:05.395
I'm here
because I have to do this.

29:05.439 --> 29:08.050
Because what happened to me
was so awful,

29:08.094 --> 29:10.705
I need to make sure it
doesn't happen to anyone else.

29:10.749 --> 29:13.708
And if you block my path here,
then I'll go to Long Beach.

29:13.752 --> 29:15.754
And if they bounce me,
then I'll try San Diego.

29:15.797 --> 29:19.018
Then Modesto or Stockton
and Fresno, Bakersfield --

29:19.061 --> 29:21.194
until someone
gives me a chance.

29:21.237 --> 29:23.326
♪♪

29:23.370 --> 29:25.589
Because I'll do whatever
it takes to be a cop.

29:25.633 --> 29:27.026
[ Groans ]

29:27.069 --> 29:30.943
♪♪

29:30.986 --> 29:33.815
Alright, five minutes.

29:33.859 --> 29:36.557
Go set up our shop.

29:36.600 --> 29:38.385
If you are this committed,
I might as well make sure

29:38.428 --> 29:39.821
that you are well-trained
before you end up

29:39.865 --> 29:41.605
at a lesser department.

29:41.649 --> 29:42.868
Yes, ma'am.

29:42.911 --> 29:44.478
Thank you.

29:44.521 --> 29:46.480
♪♪

29:46.523 --> 29:48.830
The night shift said you
were at the hotel last night.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.266
Yeah. Bailey and I
had dinner at the bar.

29:50.310 --> 29:51.702
Oh.
Two birds. One stone.

29:51.746 --> 29:53.226
How'd it go?With Claire? Or Bailey?

29:53.269 --> 29:55.228
Either? Both?

29:55.271 --> 29:57.447
Claire is definitely planning
on robbing something today.

29:57.491 --> 29:59.841
Yeah.
And Bailey is...

29:59.885 --> 30:01.800
[ Laughs ] Nice.

30:01.843 --> 30:03.018
Yeah. No. I know.

30:03.062 --> 30:05.107
[ Cellphone chimes ]

30:05.151 --> 30:07.153
Ah. Speaking of.

30:07.196 --> 30:09.677
"Thank you again
for a fantastic night.

30:09.720 --> 30:12.549
I had a lovely time, but I don't
think this is gonna work.

30:12.593 --> 30:14.421
Sorry."

30:14.464 --> 30:16.031
I don't understand.
Listen.

30:16.075 --> 30:17.772
As someone who has
been broken up with by text,

30:17.816 --> 30:20.209
I feel your pain.

30:20.253 --> 30:23.430
Yeah. Seriously, though,
I mean, we had an amazing night.

30:23.473 --> 30:24.779
I d-- I d--
What the hell?

30:24.823 --> 30:26.215
This is...

30:26.259 --> 30:27.956
I'm gonna call her.
Should I call her?

30:28.000 --> 30:30.524
Tim: 7-Adam-15, go to Channel
Nine for a status report.

30:30.567 --> 30:32.874
[ Static hisses ][ Sighs ]
No sign of Claire yet.

30:32.918 --> 30:35.050
Um, what about
the rest of her team?

30:35.094 --> 30:36.312
They're having brunch
together.

30:36.356 --> 30:38.880
Brunch? You think
they're messing with us?

30:38.924 --> 30:41.187
100%.
And that makes me nervous.

30:41.230 --> 30:43.145
Here she comes.

30:43.189 --> 30:46.105
Oh,
that is so unfortunate.

30:46.148 --> 30:47.802
You know, as a practice,

30:47.846 --> 30:49.282
you should really pay
those tickets promptly.

30:49.325 --> 30:51.153
On the bright side,
it does match.

30:51.197 --> 30:52.894
Cute.

30:52.938 --> 30:54.896
But you don't actually think
that's gonna stop me, right?

30:58.117 --> 31:04.123
Well. It doesn't matter...
who did what.

31:04.166 --> 31:06.908
My backup plans
have backup plans.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.128
[ Engine starts ]

31:09.171 --> 31:10.520
See ya.

31:10.564 --> 31:11.782
[ Engine revving ]

31:11.826 --> 31:13.654
[ Dramatic music plays ]

31:16.831 --> 31:18.833
Sergeant Bradford,
Claire just left the hotel

31:18.877 --> 31:21.401
on a black motorcycle, heading
south down Avenue of the Stars.

31:21.444 --> 31:22.837
I think they're
making their move.

31:22.881 --> 31:24.317
Surveillance teams,
get ready.

31:27.233 --> 31:29.017
[ Brakes hiss ]I've lost eyes on --

31:29.061 --> 31:30.758
Somebody get in there.

31:30.801 --> 31:33.500
All units, move in.

31:33.543 --> 31:35.850
[ Tires screech ]

31:35.894 --> 31:39.158
[ Siren wailing ]

31:39.201 --> 31:41.508
Where'd they go?In the bus.

31:41.551 --> 31:43.466
[ Tires screech ]

31:43.510 --> 31:50.691
♪♪

31:50.734 --> 31:58.133
♪♪

31:58.177 --> 32:00.222
[ Horn honks in distance ]

32:00.266 --> 32:02.050
[ Water dripping ]

32:06.098 --> 32:08.317
♪♪

32:08.361 --> 32:11.277
Control, show us
Code 6 at 3312 Bronson.

32:11.320 --> 32:13.801
A neighbor reports someone
entering our crime scene.

32:13.844 --> 32:15.368
Who are we gonna find
inside?

32:15.411 --> 32:17.979
It's either a burglar
knowing the homeowner is dead,

32:18.023 --> 32:20.416
or the killer came back

32:20.460 --> 32:22.418
to see what the police took
or left behind.

32:22.462 --> 32:24.986
At my scene, there was a
paparazzi climbing the skylight

32:25.030 --> 32:26.988
to get pictures while
the police were still there.

32:27.032 --> 32:34.996
♪♪

32:35.040 --> 32:43.004
♪♪

32:43.048 --> 32:51.012
♪♪

32:51.056 --> 32:52.796
[ Door creaking ]

32:52.840 --> 33:02.676
♪♪

33:02.719 --> 33:12.686
♪♪

33:12.947 --> 33:14.993
[ Clattering in distance ]

33:15.036 --> 33:21.608
♪♪

33:21.651 --> 33:28.006
♪♪

33:28.049 --> 33:30.095
Police!
Show me your hands.

33:30.138 --> 33:32.401
Oh, my God!
Hands up.
Turn around.

33:32.445 --> 33:34.795
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

33:34.838 --> 33:37.972
I'm Leilani. I'm Michaela's
assistant. I need her laptop.

33:38.016 --> 33:40.322
We are T-minus six hours
to red carpet.

33:40.366 --> 33:42.933
And I have a dozen clients
to dress before the Gala.

33:42.977 --> 33:44.805
A laptop wasn't found
at the house.

33:44.848 --> 33:46.198
I reviewed
the evidence logs last night

33:46.241 --> 33:47.068
while I was working
the front desk.

33:47.112 --> 33:48.461
No.
It has to be here.

33:48.504 --> 33:50.289
She didn't go
anywhere without it.

33:50.332 --> 33:53.161
And if I can't track down
Emma's choker,

33:53.205 --> 33:55.642
I might as well change my name
and go into witness protection.

33:55.685 --> 33:57.600
Wait.

33:57.644 --> 33:59.776
Michaela was coordinating the
jewelry deliveries for the Gala.

33:59.820 --> 34:01.778
Yeah.[ Chuckles ]

34:01.822 --> 34:02.953
I know what the heist is.

34:02.997 --> 34:04.129
[ Wolf Alice's "Smile" plays ]

34:04.172 --> 34:06.609
Whenever there's
an awards show or gala,

34:06.653 --> 34:09.177
celebrities borrow tens of
millions of dollars worth

34:09.221 --> 34:11.527
of bracelets, earrings,
and necklaces

34:11.571 --> 34:13.877
to bling out their gowns.

34:13.921 --> 34:17.055
They're delivered by
an armored car before the event,

34:17.098 --> 34:19.709
and then picked up again
right afterwards.

34:19.753 --> 34:22.669
Claire must've killed Michaela
to get the delivery schedule.

34:22.712 --> 34:24.758
And if she wants
to maximize the score,

34:24.801 --> 34:28.109
she'll hit the armored car
right at the beginning.

34:28.153 --> 34:30.720
♪ I scope it out,
then I throw myself into it ♪

34:30.764 --> 34:33.201
♪ I ain't ashamed in the fact
that I'm sensitive ♪

34:33.245 --> 34:35.682
♪ I believe that it is
the perfect adjective ♪

34:35.725 --> 34:38.380
♪ I wear my feelings
on my sleeve, I suggested it ♪

34:38.424 --> 34:40.861
♪ It serves me better
than to swallow in a sedative ♪

34:40.904 --> 34:43.124
♪ I am what I am,
and I'm good at it ♪

34:43.168 --> 34:44.952
♪ And you [ Tires screech ]

34:44.995 --> 34:50.131
♪♪

34:50.175 --> 34:55.267
♪♪

34:55.310 --> 34:57.312
[ Taser fires,
electricity zaps ]

34:57.356 --> 35:00.489
♪♪

35:00.533 --> 35:02.143
[ Shotgun cocks ]Put it down on the ground.

35:02.187 --> 35:12.153
♪♪

35:12.197 --> 35:14.068
[ Tires screeching ]

35:14.112 --> 35:23.164
♪♪

35:23.208 --> 35:24.644
[ Gun cocks ]

35:24.687 --> 35:29.736
♪♪

35:29.779 --> 35:34.958
♪♪

35:35.002 --> 35:36.525
Claire! Stop!

35:36.569 --> 35:37.570
[ Gunshots ]

35:37.613 --> 35:40.181
Ugh!
[ Groaning ]

35:40.225 --> 35:44.316
♪♪

35:44.359 --> 35:45.839
It's over, Claire.

35:45.882 --> 35:47.493
Throw your gun out
and come on out.

35:47.536 --> 35:49.321
I don't see myself
doing that.

35:49.364 --> 35:51.279
Oh, now,
I never took you for a quitter.

35:51.323 --> 35:53.107
I'm not a quitter.

35:53.151 --> 35:54.630
I'm just not interested
in prison.

35:54.674 --> 35:55.849
See, now, I thought
you would look at that

35:55.892 --> 35:57.851
like your next challenge.

35:57.894 --> 36:01.159
Escaping from prison?
That can't be as hard as
breaking into the Vatican.

36:01.202 --> 36:02.290
You pulled that off
well enough.

36:02.334 --> 36:03.944
Allegedly.

36:03.987 --> 36:06.512
Allegedly. Right.
Allegedly.

36:06.555 --> 36:08.514
So, what's it gonna be?
You coming out?

36:08.557 --> 36:11.647
Alright. Okay.

36:13.258 --> 36:14.563
I'm giving up.

36:14.607 --> 36:16.783
♪♪

36:16.826 --> 36:18.437
[ Groaning ]

36:18.480 --> 36:23.050
♪♪

36:23.093 --> 36:24.617
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

36:26.967 --> 36:28.360
Turn around.
Put them behind your back.

36:31.014 --> 36:32.712
Guess I underestimated you,
huh?

36:32.755 --> 36:35.280
Oh, don't feel too bad.

36:35.323 --> 36:36.411
Everyone does.[ Handcuffs click ]

36:36.455 --> 36:38.457
Ow!
Sorry.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.415
Okay. Let's go.

36:45.507 --> 36:48.597
What happened today can't
happen again if you expect
to keep those stripes.

36:48.641 --> 36:50.686
I stepped up.
I took charge.

36:50.730 --> 36:53.036
You put yourself
in the center of the action.

36:53.080 --> 36:55.387
It was the best use
of my skills.

36:55.430 --> 36:57.780
It wasn't a tactical move,
Tim.

36:57.824 --> 36:59.217
When push came to shove,

36:59.260 --> 37:01.480
you just didn't trust
anyone else to do it.

37:01.523 --> 37:04.134
Control freaks
don't make good sergeants.

37:04.178 --> 37:07.355
Look, I know you've got
decades more experience --

37:07.399 --> 37:08.748
Whoa. Hey. Wh--

37:08.791 --> 37:10.140
A decade.

37:10.184 --> 37:12.360
Okay.
But I got my own.

37:12.404 --> 37:15.233
And directing the action
from a distance works for you.

37:15.276 --> 37:17.060
I don't know
if it'll ever work for me.

37:17.104 --> 37:19.933
I need to find my own way
of being a sergeant.

37:19.976 --> 37:21.413
Fair enough.

37:21.456 --> 37:23.110
Anything else?

37:23.153 --> 37:25.155
Yeah.
It's important to give praise.

37:25.199 --> 37:27.549
An attaboy from the boss
goes a long way.

37:27.593 --> 37:29.290
[ Groans ]

37:29.334 --> 37:30.596
It's against my nature...

37:30.639 --> 37:33.294
but I will give it
a shot.

37:33.338 --> 37:35.296
Make sure you
check the shop thoroughly

37:35.340 --> 37:36.993
after you turn in
your war bags.

37:37.037 --> 37:38.865
Yes, ma'am.

37:38.908 --> 37:41.346
Detective Harper --
Can I ask you a favor?

37:41.389 --> 37:42.825
Do you think you can
give me another nickname

37:42.869 --> 37:45.175
rather than five minutes?Why?

37:47.917 --> 37:49.919
'Cause that's about
how long Patrick was alive

37:49.963 --> 37:51.443
after his throat was cut.

37:51.486 --> 37:52.835
He crawled
out of the shower.

37:52.879 --> 37:54.228
Looking for help.
Looking for me.

37:54.272 --> 37:56.622
If I had just woken up,
he might still be alive.

37:56.665 --> 37:58.754
I'm sorry.
I didn't -- I didn't know.

37:58.798 --> 38:00.321
Yeah.

38:00.365 --> 38:01.627
Look. I'm not looking
for any special treatment.

38:01.670 --> 38:04.456
I just --Hey, don't worry about it.

38:04.499 --> 38:08.895
After your solve today,
you get a little more leash.

38:08.938 --> 38:12.812
And besides, coming up
with nicknames is fun for me.

38:12.855 --> 38:14.683
[ Chuckles ]

38:14.727 --> 38:17.686
Yes, ma'am.

38:17.730 --> 38:19.471
I look forward to hearing
what you come up with.

38:19.514 --> 38:21.908
♪ I was afraid of me

38:21.951 --> 38:25.520
♪ I was afraid to see
